  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "Yes, every student admitted to the **Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISER)** receives a fellowship as part of their program. IISERs are prestigious institutions in India that focus on research and education in basic sciences. The fellowships are provided to support students financially during their studies and to encourage them to pursue research.\n\nFor undergraduate students (BS-MS dual degree program), a monthly fellowship is provided starting from the third year of their program, typically contingent on meeting certain academic criteria.\n\nFor postgraduate students (e.g., MS, PhD), fellowships are provided as per the norms of the relevant funding agencies (e.g., CSIR, UGC, INSPIRE, or IISER's own funding). The amount and eligibility criteria may vary depending on the program and funding source.\n\nIt\u2019s important to check the specific guidelines of the IISER you\u2019re interested in, as the details may vary slightly between campuses.",
